<paragraph id="8BB7368AD863FFEC3CB4FCA2314CF82D" blockId="54.[151,1058,791,843]" pageId="54" pageNumber="1013">
E t y m o l o g y: The trivial name, 
<emphasis id="B97CEA98D863FFEC3E09FCA230B3F84B" box="[554,652,792,813]" italics="true" pageId="54" pageNumber="1013">cnecostus</emphasis>
, is a Greek adjective that stems from 
<emphasis id="B97CEA98D863FFEC3CB4FC8F32E3F82C" box="[151,220,821,842]" italics="true" pageId="54" pageNumber="1013">knekos</emphasis>
(= pale yellow); with regards to the coloration of the elytral disc.
</paragraph>
